The correct answer is B. Data Processing. Data science uses various data processing techniques to translate category data (also known as categorical data) into numerical values. This process is called encoding or transformation, and it allows categorical data to be used in machine learning models and other numerical analyses. Some common techniques used for this purpose include: 1. One-hot encoding 2. Label encoding 3. Ordinal encoding These techniques enable data scientists to convert categorical data into numerical representations that can be processed and analyzed using statistical and machine learning methods.
